    "population": "N: 81 (Egyptian) Sex: m=52, f=29 Age: 20 (3-58) WT: 48.4 (15-75)",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“This paper describes a developed pharmacokinetic model for the estimation of valproic acid (VPA) clearance (CL) calculated from routine clinical data taken from Egyptian epileptic patients.”",
    "covariates": "Tested: AGE, WT. SEX, DDVPA, Comedication (CBZ, DDCBZ), INDI (indication) Included: AGE, DDVPA, CBZ, INDI",
    "observations": "Model shows good predictive capacity in PRED scattergram. Model made with retrospective clinical data, backward deletion. No attempt was made to estimate relative F between formulations. They fitted a model with a bolus input and fixed the value of V at 0.22 l kg. A nonlinear relationship is found between CL and Age, WT, and DDVPA. In addition, VPA CL increased with comedication (CBZ) and in uncontrolled epilepsy patients.",
    "dose": "Steady state, oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "one-compartment model, first order elimination and absorption",
    "equations": "CL = ((theta1+(theta2*CBZ)+(theta3*DOSE)+(theta4*(AGE/20))+ (theta5*INDI)))*(1+eta1) V = theta6 Kel = theta7 KA = theta8 CHILD: KA=4 (oral tablet) ADULT: KA=1 (EC tablet) Cobs=Cipred *(1+eps1 ) DOSE: VPA dose in mg/day AGE: Age in years CBZ: comedication carbamazepine (Yes:1, No:0) INDI: Indication uncontrolled epilepsy (Yes:1, No:0)",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=0.105 theta2=0.151 theta3=0.000248 theta4=0.0968 theta5=0.0803 theta6=11.6 theta7=0.19 theta8=1 omega1=0.0529 sigma1=5.24",
    "validation": "Qualification group of 20 children"
  },
